            <span id="BigFirstLetterText">P</span>opo is my grandma, and I admire her for her strength and her perseverance. I can only imagine the hardships that she went through raising her children under the limited financial circumstances she was in when she was married with four kids. It's interesting to me that she didn't have someone to tell her, "Stay strong. Be patient with your husband. Be patient with your kids." Nothing like that. She just believed in it herself that one day, all of this hard work was going to pay off. She didn't have religion at that time. She didn't have a belief or faith until much, much later—right before she passed away. It amazes me that she had such perseverance through the trials she went through in her marriage and raising children.  <br />
